According to a statement issued on January 14, 2021, the number of United States military troops in Afghanistan is currently at its lowest point in 19 years. Similarly, the number of troops in Iraq and Syria is also at its lowest in many years. The statement emphasizes a commitment to ending endless wars and expresses pride in rebuilding the military and providing support to the men and women in uniform. It also highlights a $2.5 trillion investment in new equipment, all made in the U.S.A.